      • Vin: a unique VIN of the form xHCMxxxxxxxxxxxxx where x is replaced by digits

  • Method Details

    • uiReadyVehicle

      public static VehicleBuilder uiReadyVehicle()
      Creates a builder which will fill out the fields required in vehicle UI pages:
      • License plate set to a unique value using withUniqueLicensePlate
      • Vin set to a unique value using the default VIN pattern used by new VehicleBuilder()
      • Color: Black
      • Make: Honda
      • Model: Civic
      • State: CA
      • Style: Passenger Car
      • Year: 2000
      Returns:
      a new builder

    • advanceUniqueIdCounters

      public static void advanceUniqueIdCounters(int amountToAdvance)
      Advance the counters used to generate unique license plate and VIN. Not to be used in normal smoke tests. Used by ISO round trip tests to avoid the massive match reports that result if we repeatedly re-use the same VIN and license plate numbers by re-running the same test over and over. This is an inefficient method so the amountToAdvance shouldn't be too large - certainly less than 100,000. If any of this confuses you don't use this method.
      Parameters:
      amountToAdvance - amount to advance the counters; typically a random number.
